default, the three operators employ 
defaultover 10,000 people
default. In 2012, they carried
default around 3 million 
defaultpassengers using a fleet of 
defaultnearly 1,000
default helicopters. 
default&#xa0;
default1.3
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIn the UK, the operators together employ 
defaultalmost 2,000 
defaultpeople. 
defaultIn 2012, they carried over half a million 
defaultpassengers to installations in the North Sea 
defaultwith a combined 
defaultUK fleet of over 80 helicopters. Over the period from 1981 to 2010, there were almost 3 million flight hours in the UK Continental Shelf sector of the North Sea with over 54 million passengers carried. 
