default&#xa0;default2.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAs operators, 
defaultit is 
defaultour duty above all else is to provide the safest possible operating environment for our crews and passengers. All three operators are dedicated to safety – not only independently, as commercial organisations driving quality 
defaultand safety 
defaultfor our customers through innovation, but also increasingly in collaboration. 
default&#xa0;
default2.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultNotwithstanding our collective commitment to safety, the North Sea oil and gas industry operates in a challenging environment and there are many inherent risks. 
default 
defaultAberdeen is home to the largest helicopter operation in the world and is considered one of the safest. A recent study commissioned by the UK Offshore Oil and Gas Industry Association Limited
default found that for the period from 1995 to 2010, the safety record of helicopter operations in the UK Continental Shelf compared favourably with other operations in the North Sea and those elsewhere in the world. The following table compares the global fatal and non-fatal accident rates of UK Continental Shelf helicopter operations from 1995 to 2010 with all North Sea and worldwide operations, based on 100,000 flying hours.
