default&#xa0;default4.5
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultEnsuring safety is not just about reducing technical risks. 
defaultThe managing of h
defaultuman factors play
defaults
default an important role in aviation 
defaultsafety
default. Training of crews and pilots is critical to our approach to safety, especially as the aircraft used are increasingly more complex. Flight crew simulators are now routinely used and these are increasingly sophisticated and able to replicate the characteristics of the aircraft we use, as well as different weather conditions and approaches. There are three simulator training locations in Aberdeen. Training packages are approved by the relevant authorities and include packages which replicate the flying conditions for both routine operations and emergency procedures.
default&#xa0;default4.6
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultOperators also use mandatory Crew Resource Management training programmes designed to 
defaultpromote positive 
defaultcrew behaviour and improve performance in the cockpit.  This training includes situational awareness, decision making, threat and error management and crew cooperation. 
default&#xa0;
